cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with segmentation of tubular structures such as vessels and roads. It also proposes a novel similarity measure and loss function for training neural segmentation networks. 

It could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it proposes a differentiable loss function for training neural networks. 

Additionally, it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it deals with training neural networks. 

Finally, it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with segmentation of 2D and 3D images.
